          "l": "খ", "m": 4,
          "q": "Show that \\(P\\), \\(Q\\), \\(R\\) are collinear.",
          "sol": [
            {"t": "Slope of PQ:"},
            {"m": "m_{PQ} = \\frac{6-2}{5-1} = \\frac{4}{4} = 1"},
            {"t": "Slope of PR:"},
            {"m": "m_{PR} = \\frac{4-2}{3-1} = \\frac{2}{2} = 1"},
            {"t": "Since \\(m_{PQ} = m_{PR} = 1\\), the three points are collinear. ✓"}
          ]
        },
        {
          "l": "গ", "m": 4,
          "q": "Find the equation of the line passing through these points.",
          "sol": [
            {"t": "Using point-slope form with point P(1,2) and slope m=1:"},
            {"m": "y - 2 = 1(x - 1)"},
            {"m": "\\boxed{y = x + 1}"},
            {"note": "Verify: Q(5,6): 6 = 5+1 ✓, R(3,4): 4 = 3+1 ✓"}
          ]
        }
      ]
